**Paytunia** is a web and mobile [[browser-based_wallet]] developed by [[Paymium]]. The mobile and web clients are front-ends to a hosted Bitcoin wallet. Paymium also operates the [[Bitcoin-Central]] exchange and all exchange accounts are accessible through Paytunia's web and mobile wallet as well.

##API
A [Ruby gem](https://github.com/paytunia/paytunia) and [well-documented API](https://github.com/paytunia/api-documentation) are available.

##History

* 2012-Apr-05 - [[Paymium]] announces the service. (3.1)

* 2013-Apr-01 - Paytunia was suspended due to a security breach. User funds were safe. On April 5, the service was announced to resume operation. However, as of April 28, the website still only displays the security announcements. (3.2)

